    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="374"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.61351/47a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Food
                        Administrator</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hoover</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: You are informed that the Cuban Minister called
                    at this Department and stated that his Government was informed that it was the
                    purpose of the United States Food Administration to fix a price for sugar, and
                    that his Government had instructed him to request that no definite action be
                    taken in this respect until after the Cuban Government had been given an
                    opportunity to acquaint <pb facs="0452" n="340" xml:id="pg_340"/> the Food
                    Administration of its views on this subject. The Cuban Minister added that he
                    was prepared at any time to discuss this matter with you.</p>
                <p>The Cuban Minister was informed that his Government’s request would be
                    communicated at once to you.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Second Assistant Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
